{{Quote|Mandalorians believe confrontation is required for growth, on the personal as well as the cultural level. War is the Mandalorian way of life.|Jedi Master [[Gnost-Dural]]|audio=MandoBeliefs-Timeline3.flac|<ref name="Timeline3">{{TORweb|url=holonet/galactic-history|text=Timeline 3: The Return of the Mandalorians|int=Timeline 3: The Return of the Mandalorians}}</ref>}}
[[File:Mandalorian_Armors.jpg|thumb|right|260px|A [[Mandalorian Crusaders|Mandalorian Crusader]], a [[Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders/Legends|Mandalorian Neo-Crusader]] and a [[Death Watch/Legends|Death Watch]] warrior, three incarnations of the Mandalorian shock trooper.]]
'''Mandalorian shock trooper''' was a collective term referring to the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] combatants who followed the way of the traditional Mandalorian warrior. The concept of shock trooper therefore encompassed many different groups of Mandalorians throughout history, with sometimes apparently very little in common.<ref name="THoM">{{InsiderCite|80|The History of the Mandalorians: Exploring the Evolution of a Mighty Race of Warriors}}</ref> In any case, Mandalorian shock troopers could be defined as the Mandalorians who respected the ancient [[Canons of Honor]],<ref name="TCSWE-Mst">{{CSWECite|II|284|Mandalorian shock troopers}}</ref> a code aiming to lead any warrior to attain glory though combat and loyalty to a clan. Mandalorian shock troopers were easily recognizable for their distinct [[Mandalorian armor/Legends|Mandalorian-styled armor]].<ref name="THoM" />

==History==
{{Quote|In five millennia, the Mandalorians fought with and against a thousand armies on a thousand worlds. They learned to speak as many languages and absorbed weapons technology and tactics from every war.|[[Mandalorians: Identity and Language]]|<ref name="Republic Commando: Triple Zero">''[[Republic Commando: Triple Zero]]''</ref>}}
The tradition of Mandalorian shock trooper dated back to the legendary [[Taung/Legends|Taung Shadow Warriors]].<ref name="THoM" /> The Taungs fought epic [[Zhell–Taung war|battles]] on the ancient [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] and eventually settled the planet [[Mandalore/Legends|Mandalore]], becoming the first Mandalorians.<ref name="TCSWE-Taung">{{CSWECite|III|225|Taung}}</ref> Although the species eventually vanished, [[Human/Legends|Humans]] and other species of Mandalorians continued the Taung warrior tradition as the Mandalorian shock troopers.<ref name="THoM" />

[[File:Mandalorians_-_TEA.jpg|thumb|left|250px|[[Mandalorian Crusaders]], one of the earliest groups of Mandalorian shock troopers.]]
The first Mandalorian shock troopers identified as such were the [[Mandalorian Crusaders]] who waged violent and rather primitive [[Mandalorian Crusades|crusades]] during several centuries. These fierce warriors were finally defeated by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] during the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]] around [[4000 BBY/Legends|4000 BBY]]. In the next decades, their successor, the [[Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders/Legends|Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders]], assembled a powerful army in prevision of an apocalyptic war. They conquered many worlds in the so-called [[Mandalorian Wars]], ultimately declaring a total war to the Republic. Although the Neo-Crusaders were defeated and decimated, the Mandalorian culture survived. However, for the next 2,000 years, the few remaining shock troopers would never be united and served almost exclusively as [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]]. Mandalorian shock troopers therefore fought as mercenaries in the majority of the major galactic conflicts,<ref name="THoM" /> including the [[Great Galactic War]],<ref name="Timeline3" /> the [[War against Zakuul]],<ref name="kotfe">{{TORcite|exp=kotfe|chapter=14}}</ref> and the [[New Sith Wars]].<ref name="THoM" />

[[File:MandalorianProtectors-GAW.jpg|thumb|right|200px|[[Mandalorian Protectors (Spar)|Mandalorian Protectors]], one of the latest groups of Mandalorian shock troopers.]]

The reunification of the Mandalorian shock troopers began in the century prior to the fall of the Republic, when the former [[Journeyman Protector/Legends|Journeyman Protector]] [[Jaster Mereel]] created the [[Supercommando Codex]]. This new code was a revived and modernized version of the millennium-old Canons of Honor with stronger principles of ethics and honor. A number of clans accepted to follow Mereel's creed but a splinter group of ruthless and amoral Mandalorians known as the [[Death Watch/Legends|Death Watch]] rejected it. Eventually, the ideological conflict turned to [[Mandalorian Civil War (True Mandalorians)|civil war]] and all the Mandalorian shock troopers roughly organized onto two camps: Jaster Mereel's [[True Mandalorians]] and [[Tor Vizsla]]'s Death Watch. The two factions were virtually annihilated during the conflict<ref name="THoM" /> but both groups later rose from the ashes during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="TCW">''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' television series</ref><ref name="THoM" /> The Death Watch rose under the leadership of [[Pre Vizsla/Legends|Pre Vizsla]] and his shock troopers [[Battle of Mandalore/Legends|fought]] the Republic-backed [[New Mandalorians/Legends|New Mandalorians]] for the control of the planet Mandalore.<ref name="TCW" /> Meanwhile, the former [[Advanced Recon Commando/Legends|ARC trooper]] [[Spar]] assembled a small army of [[Mandalorian Supercommando|supercommandos]] named the [[Mandalorian Protectors (Spar)|Mandalorian Protectors]] inspired by Jaster Mereel's True Mandalorians. These protectors sided with the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] in the war against the Republic. By the end end of the Clone Wars, most of the Mandalorian shock troopers had been killed in combat. However, the Mandalorian Protectors emerged as the main force of Mandalorian shock troopers.<ref name="THoM" />

The Mandalorian Protectors strengthened after the end of the Clone Wars and the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] under the leadership of [[Fenn Shysa]]. Mandalorian shock troopers eventually [[Battle of the City of Bone|freed]] Mandalore from the Imperial presence and sided with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] and the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. In the next decades, the Mandalorian Protectors became the main defense force of the [[Mandalore sector/Legends|Mandalore sector]] and Mandalorian shock troopers fought bravely against the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]].<ref name="THoM" />

